  "text": "Per and post-cardioversion: echocardiography can be used for monitoring the heart recovery (LA, LAA but also LV stunning). [CITATION_1] The difficulty is that the duration of that stunning is variable and has not been extensively studied during the 3 weeks following a cardioversion despite the recommended duration of the anticoagulation of 3 weeks after the cardioversion that one is classically considering. [CITATION_2] ",
